Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to
the boil.

Add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them
sticking together.

== Beef and Pepper ==

Meanwhile, halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice
into thin strips.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and sliced pepper, then sprinkle
over the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}. Add less if you'd prefer things milder.

Fry until the mince is browned and the pepper has softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

== Sauce and Ribbons ==

Meanwhile, cut the @lime{1/2}(cut into wedges). Trim and peel the
@carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the
carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @ketjap manis{50%g}, @honey{15%g},
@soy sauce{25%ml} and @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}. Add a good squeeze of lime
juice from a lime wedge and mix well.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

== Finishing ==

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat from the beef.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the sauce and carrot ribbons to the mince.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles to the mince.

Stir to coat the noodles in the sauce and cook until everything's piping hot,
~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{?splash} if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Share the Thai inspired beef noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!